{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Zeng et al. (2024) suggest that extending training duration and providing targeted programs can enhance interdisciplinary competencies among teachers.",
    "The outcomes of these PD initiatives often show increased self-efficacy and confidence among teachers, enabling them to engage more effectively with STEM content (Geng et al. 2019; Lin et al. 2024; Mao et al. 2023).",
    "Teachers who participated in such programs report a better understanding of STEM principles and more confidence in implementing innovative teaching methods, such as projectbased learning and technology integration (Ong et al. 2020; Huang et al. 2022).",
    "Approaches and Influencing Factors.",
    "Evaluated PD programs frequently utilize experiential and investigative learning activities to develop teachers' skills in delivering STEM education effectively (Huang et al. 2022; Lin et al. 2023; Zhang et al. 2023)."
  ]
}